r  i-ljuser  i-ljuser-type-P     \"  data-ljuser=\"seanan_mcguire\" lj:user=\"seanan_mcguire\" ><a href=\"http://seanan-mcguire.livejournal.com/profile\"  target=\"_self\"  class=\"i-ljuser-profile\" ><img  class=\"i-ljuser-userhead\"  src=\"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10\" /></a><a href=\"http://seanan-mcguire.livejournal.com/\" class=\"i-ljuser-username\"   target=\"_self\"   ><b>seanan_mcguire</b></a></span> and <span  class=\"ljuser  i-ljuser  i-ljuser-type-P     \"  data-ljuser=\"gailcarriger\" lj:user=\"gailcarriger\" ><a href=\"http://gailcarriger.livejournal.com/profile\"  target=\"_self\"  class=\"i-ljuser-profile\" ><img  class=\"i-ljuser-userhead\"  src=\"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10\" /></a><a href=\"http://gailcarriger.livejournal.com/\" class=\"i-ljuser-username\"   target=\"_self\"   ><b>gailcarriger</b></a></span>, I am excited to see both of their names up for the Campbell, and am fervently hoping for a tie, so I don't have to feel bad for one or the other.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"7 years ago","ctime":"April 5 2010, 02:13:38 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://tsgeisel.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"tsgeisel","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"tsgeisel","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://tsgeisel.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"tsgeisel","ctime_ts":"1270433618","tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/91237832/7059164","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/145074.html?replyto=9585074","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/145074.html?thread=9585074#t9585074","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/145074.html?thread=9585074#t9585074","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/145074.html?thread=9585074#t9585074","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"grrm","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":9585074,"talkid":37441,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/145074.html?thread=9585074#t9585074","upictitle":"George R.R. Martin: Spain","article":"Looking over this year's list of Hugo finalists, the thing that leapt out at me most were the nominees in the three short fiction categories, novella, novelette, and short story.<br /><br />What's startling about this year's list -- to me at least, being the dinosaur that I am -- is that the traditional paper magazines are hardly represented, after decades of dominating these three categories. There are three stories from ASIMOV's and one from INTERZONE... but nothing from F&SF, nothing from ANALOG, nothing from REALMS OF FANTASY. Instead we have nominees coming from e-magazines, websites, small press mags, and anthologies.<br /><br />The times they are a-changin', I guess.<br /><br />I suspect this will only hasten the oft-predicted end of the traditional genre magazines. The conventional wisdom, up until very recently, was that you could maybe get better money selling to an anthology or an e-mag, but if you wanted a Hugo nomination, the old digests were still the place to be. <br /><br />Not any more, it would seem. And given how little they pay, if they are no longer the awards showcase they were, one wonders why anyone would want to give them first look at a strong story.<br /><br />End of an epoch, maybe?","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"7 years ago","ctime":"April 5 2010, 04:38:08 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Further Reflections on the Hugo Nominees","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"grrm","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"grrm","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"grrm","ctime_ts":"1270442288","tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/51443191/3030116","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/145074.html?replyto=9587890","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/145074.html?thread=9587890#t9587890","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/145074.html?thread=9587890#t9587890","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/145074.html?thread=9587890#t9587890","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"hippoiathanatoi","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://hippoiathanatoi.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":9587890,"talkid":37452,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/145074.html?thread=9587890#t9587890","above":9585074,"upictitle":"Elio &amp; Linda: Elio","article":"To what degree does a non-North American location explain this? The percentage of non-N.A. attendees will be way up, I'd guess, and I'd further guess that reading the traditional magazines is less common outside of the U.S. and Canada. Webzines and sites like Tor.com are certainly a lot more available in Australia than Asimov's, F&SF, and Analog, at a guess.<br /><br />That said, I'm reminded of <span  class=\"ljuser  i-ljuser  i-ljuser-type-P     \"  data-ljuser=\"clarkesworld\" lj:user=\"clarkesworld\" ><a href=\"http://clarkesworld.livejournal.com/profile\"  target=\"_self\"  class=\"i-ljuser-profile\" ><img  class=\"i-ljuser-userhead\"  src=\"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10\" /></a><a href=\"http://clarkesworld.livejournal.com/\" class=\"i-ljuser-username\"   target=\"_self\"   ><b>clarkesworld</b></a></span>'s <a href=\"http://clarkesworld.livejournal.com/151307.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">chart</a> showing the increasing presence of online fiction in Locus Magazine's end-of-year recommendation lists. It's a definite trend, and it's going to keep going. End of an epoch, indeed.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"7 years ago","below":9589938,"ctime":"April 5 2010, 17:10:02 UTC","parent":9585074,"massactions":0,"subject":"Re: Further Reflections on the Hugo Nominees","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://hippoiathanatoi.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"hippoiathanatoi","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"hippoiathanatoi","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://hippoiathanatoi.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"hippoiathanatoi","ctime_ts":"1270487402","tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/121313083/9947615","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/145074.html?replyto=9589938","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/145074.html?thread=9589938#t9589938","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/145074.html?thread=9589938#t9589938","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/145074.html?thread=9589938#t9589938","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"douglascohen","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://douglascohen.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":9589938,"talkid":37460,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/145074.html?thread=9589938#t9589938","above":9587890,"upictitle":"Douglas Cohen: pic#121313083","article":"Believe it or not, RoF has never snagged a Hugo recommendation.  Nebulas, but no Hugos.<br /><br />As to where to sell your shorts ...shrug.  I have an obvious bias for RoF since I work with that mag, but I don't think there is a such thing as a perfect market.  Everyone is better than someone in some respect, be it response times, readership numbers, who offers illustrations to stories, which venues win the awards, pay rates, method of submission, how long you have to wait to see an accepted story published, etc.  I think it all boils down to what is most important to each writer.     ","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"7 years ago","below":9593778,"ctime":"April 5 2010, 19:54:35 UTC","parent":9585074,"massactions":0,"subject":"Re: Further Reflections on the Hugo Nominees","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://douglascohen.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"douglascohen","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"douglascohen","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://douglascohen.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"douglascohen","ctime_ts":"1270497275","tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/16406488/3544187","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/145074.html?replyto=9593778","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/145074.html?thread=9593778#t9593778","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/145074.html?thread=9593778#t9593778","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href"