n tell us which you like best? My understanding is you read alot of science fiction and fantasy. I have seen alot of positive reviews of boneshaker. The guys at Elitist Book Reviews (some of Brandon sanderson's friends) did not like it. <br /><br />I have liked Robert Sawyer in the past. I liked Flash Forward (the TV show is VERY different from the book). <br /><br />You write in the genre and we like your writing, if you have a few minutes could you do a short blog on which stories you liked best (of the ones you read) or maybe your favorites for the past year? Would help me with my reading list. I like to read books that authors I like recommend. <br /><br />Here is one book tip from me. You said you like the Pillars of the Earth. Check out The Cathedral of the Sea. It is a translation from spanish, but very good. Takes place in Barcelona in the late middle ages. The authors does a VERY good job talking about the culture and politics of the city while being entertaining. ","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"7 years ago","ctime":"April 6 2010, 13:02:31 UTC","parent":9585586,"massactions":0,"subject":"What are your favorites for the award?","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://guessingo.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"guessingo","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"guessingo","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://guessingo.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"guessingo","ctime_ts":"1270558951","tracked":0}]}